Student Portfolio Website - Javascript, HTML, CSS
Course: INFR 3120 - Web and Scripting Programming at Ontario Tech University
Student: Shifa Faisal

Link to website: https://shifas-portfolio-uzzn.onrender.com/ 

Project Overview -
Personal portfolio website built using Node,js Javascript HTML5 and CSS3.
Contains four pages describing and showcasing the student's life, skills, projects and option to contact:
Home page
About Me page
Projects Page
Contact Me page


Structure -
The project is organized into separate HTML, ejs, Node.js and JS files for the content contained in the webpage, and CSS files for the styling and responsive design of the website.
Node modules - contains all installed dependencies from npm 
Public - holds all files accessible in browser
Asset - images, and other media
Script - JS files for client site
Routes - holds route handlers that define websiteâ€™s url
Index - routes for home, about, project, content pages
Users - user related routes
Views - holds ejs template files
Partials - reusable page components (header, footer, main navigation)
Contact, About, Error, Index, Projects - templates for different pages \
App -sets up routes and configuration for Express
Server - starts Node.js
Package - metadata
Package-lock - auto generated file, locks versions 

Color Theme -
Used Adobe Color Palette to find a colour scheme suitable to both the owner's choice and web design.
Deeper red and neutral colours to create both an elegant and professional aesthetic.
Use of dark and light shades provide a balance.

Colour Scheme:
#0D0D0D, #6CA6D9, #275D8C, #022340, #033159, White

